          "title": "The kingdom has come upon you — and the Spirit cannot be blasphemed without cost",
          "body": "The Beelzebul controversy (22-32) contains Matthew's clearest realized-eschatological claim: 'If I cast out demons by the Spirit of God, then the kingdom of God has come upon you' (28). The exorcisms are not merely compassionate; they are *the kingdom arriving* — the strong man bound (29), his house plundered. To call this the work of Satan (24) is to slander the Spirit by whom the kingdom is breaking in (31-32). The unforgivable sin is not a single ill-considered word but a settled, willful identification of the Spirit's witness as demonic — the closing of the only door through which forgiveness comes."
